# Monorepo Conventions

Turborepo + pnpm workspaces. Apps are thin; reusable capability lives in packages.

## Where things go

- `apps/*` — deployable Next.js apps, one per market. App-specific composition only.
- `packages/ui` — shared React components + Tailwind theme/design tokens.
- `packages/cms` — Sanity client, GROQ helpers, schemas, `market` convention.
- `packages/tradetracker` — feed fetch/parse/normalize.
- `packages/utils` — framework-agnostic helpers.
- `packages/config` — shared `tsconfig` + ESLint flat configs.

## Rules

- Packages are named `@odyssey/*`. Import across packages via the package name, e.g.
  `import { Button } from '@odyssey/ui'` — **never** deep relative paths like
  `../../packages/ui/src/...`.
- Add cross-package deps with `"workspace:*"` and list them in the app's `transpilePackages`
  (see `apps/albanie/next.config.ts`).
- Shared tsconfig/eslint come from `@odyssey/config`; don't redefine base rules per package.
- If code is used by more than one app, move it into a package instead of duplicating.
- Prefer `pnpm --filter <pkg>` for scoped work; run `pnpm build/lint/type-check` from root
  (Turbo) before finishing.
